🏠 California House Price Prediction using Machine Learning

This project implements a Machine Learning Regression Model to predict house prices in California using the California Housing Dataset from Scikit-learn. The project covers the complete data science workflow, including data preprocessing, exploratory data analysis (EDA), feature correlation analysis, model training, prediction, and performance evaluation.

The objective is to build an accurate regression model capable of estimating house prices based on various housing features such as median income, house age, average rooms, average bedrooms, population, average occupancy, latitude, and longitude.

